### 1. Health check
GET http://localhost:3000/api/health

### 2. Register
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "parola123secure",
    "name": "John Doe"
}

### 3. Register — duplicate email (409)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "altaparola1",
    "name": "Alt John"
}

### 4. Login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "parola123secure"
}

### 5. Login — wrong password (401)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "gresita"
}

### 6. Access protected route with token
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN

### 7. Access protected route without token (401)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me

### 8. Refresh token — get new access token (old refresh token is invalidated)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refreshToken": "PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN"
}

### 9. Reuse old refresh token (401 — rotation in action)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refreshToken": "PASTE_SAME_OLD_REFRESH_TOKEN"
}

### 10. Create article (authenticated)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/articles
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN

{
    "title": "Securitatea API-urilor",
    "content": "JWT si OAuth sunt esentiale pentru securizarea API-urilor RESTful."
}

### 11. Create article without token (401)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/articles
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Nu ar trebui sa mearga",
    "content": "Fara token"
}

### 12. Get all articles (public, no auth needed)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/articles

### 13. Delete article as regular user (403 — admin only)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/articles/1
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN

### 14. Google OAuth login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "idToken": "PASTE_GOOGLE_ID_TOKEN"
}

### 15. Google OAuth — invalid token (401)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "idToken": "token.invalid.here"
}

### 16. Logout — invalidate refresh token
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refreshToken": "PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN"
}
